  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Last four keys of the top row, and they go to your two weakest fingers: ring (W, O) and pinky (Q, P). They're clumsier than the others, so we give them a little extra patience. Get these and you own the whole top row."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "W is a left-ring reach, O is a right-ring reach. Q is a left-pinky stretch, P is a right-pinky stretch. Pinky is the wild card - slow and deliberate beats fast and sloppy. Keep your anchors on F and J, reach up, snap back."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🤏",
      "title": "Pinky needs patience",
      "text": "Your pinky doesn't take orders as well as the rest. Don't fight it, don't rush it. One calm tap per key, return home. Slow now means fast later - that's the deal."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "w o w o w o w o w o w o w o w o w o w o",
      "finger": "orange",
